{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: a unit test on only the file-filter function can miss wiring bugs between PR changed-file collection, path normalization, and scan dispatch. REAL-INFRA: no real network/OS subprocess is strictly required if changed-file input is injected and filesystem is local. MOCK-HIDE: pure mocks of all collaborators could hide incorrect module integration.","test_description":"Run the lint step end-to-end in-process with a temporary repo snapshot and a realistic changed-files list fixture (including renamed/nested paths). Assert scanner invocations occur only for changed files and zero reads/scans happen for unchanged files.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: unit-testing only formatter logic can miss failures in aggregation -> grouping -> comment payload assembly. REAL-INFRA: real GitHub API is not required to catch grouping defects; a local API client stub sink is sufficient. MOCK-HIDE: over-mocking intermediate structures can hide miswired severity mapping.","test_description":"Execute aggregation and comment-construction modules together using mixed-severity findings input. Capture the outbound comment payload via a stubbed GitHub client and assert all findings are grouped under error/warning/info sections with correct counts/content placement.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: mocked linter/runtime timing will not reveal true throughput, process startup, or I/O overhead. REAL-INFRA: this is explicitly bounded by GitHub Actions wall-clock timeout and depends on OS/subprocess performance. MOCK-HIDE: replacing linter subprocess/file I/O with mocks can make tests always pass while real CI times out.","test_description":"Run a system performance test in CI-like conditions with 200 representative files and the real linter execution path (including subprocesses). Measure end-to-end elapsed time for changed-file collection, analysis, and comment generation; fail if >= 10 minutes (prefer safety threshold, e.g., 8-9 minutes).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: in-process exception mocks do not reliably represent real subprocess crash modes (non-zero exit, signal, partial output). REAL-INFRA: requires real subprocess behavior and orchestration recovery handling. MOCK-HIDE: mocking linter calls as normal return values can hide failure-continuation bugs.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline with the real linter subprocess against a corpus containing one crash-triggering malformed file plus valid files. Assert the run records the crash for that file, continues analyzing subsequent files, and still emits/posts a final aggregated result.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: core failure boundary is deterministic dedup logic over finding tuples (file, line, rule/signature, severity/message). REAL-INFRA: no OS/network/subprocess dependency is required to validate correctness. MOCK-HIDE: limited risk if inputs model real finding schema; integration adds confidence but is not minimum.","test_description":"Unit-test the dedup function with crafted findings containing intentional same-line overlaps across rules and repeated identical emits. Assert output keeps one canonical entry per dedup key while preserving distinct non-duplicates on nearby lines/rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
